<subSubSection id="D6D06521FFF0FFDE9A81FB5BFBC76F3D" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E7536AAFFF0FFDE9A81FB5BFBC76F3D" blockId="6.[151,1126,1199,1416]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">
Body length 
<quantity id="59329B4FFFF0FFDE990DFB5BFD536ED2" box="[603,732,1200,1224]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="721" unit="mm" value="4.95" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="4.2">
4.2 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE992AFB5BFD066EDD" bold="true" box="[636,649,1200,1224]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
5.7 mm
</quantity>
. Body completely orange or tibiae and metaventrite black. Antennae longer than body, antennomere III about 1.5 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE98FAFB3BFC366EFD" bold="true" box="[940,953,1232,1256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
3.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Pronotum 1.3 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF0FFDE995AFB1BFD966F1D" bold="true" box="[524,537,1264,1288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">–</emphasis>
1.4 times as wide as long, covered with fine dense punctures. Elytra glabrous. Aedeagus simple, long, thin, with long internal sclerite (
<figureCitation id="06F12A2FFFF0FFDE98BAFAFBFBB46F3D" box="[1004,1083,1296,1320]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="721">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
